<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-47-0018 </DOCNO><TEXT>A number of demonstration projects has been undertaken recently in theNordic countries, in relation to the utilization of domestic sourcesof renewable energy. The Nordic Council of Ministers had arranged a seriesof one-day seminars where experts from each member country could presentand jointly evaluate the results. The themes planned to be presentedwere the use of solar and geothermal energy, wind power and organic wastesas sources of energy production (Denmark), underground storage of heat,natural gas and oil (Sweden), wave energy (Norway), biomass and turfas sources of energy (Finland) and geothermal energy and heat production(Iceland). Aspects of environmental protection were also to be discussed.(AB).</TEXT></DOC>